ange?\r\n\r\nFix issue: https://github.com/rclone/rclone/issues/8248\r\n\r\n#### Was the change discussed in an issue or in the forum before?\r\n\r\nNo, it wasn't.\r\n\r\n#### Checklist\r\n\r\n- [X] I have read the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#submitting-a-new-feature-or-bug-fix).\r\n- [X] I have added tests for all changes in this PR if appropriate.\r\n- [X] I have added documentation for the changes if appropriate.\r\n- [X] All commit messages are in [house style](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#commit-messages).\r\n- [X] I'm done, this Pull Request is ready for review :-)\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/8263/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/8263/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/2566975855","html_url":"https://github.com/rclone/rclone/issues/8248#issuecomment-2566975855","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/8248","id":2566975855,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAQ-n5M6ZAPFv","user":{"login":"hiddenmarten","id":114359669,"node_id":"U_kgDOBtD9dQ","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/114359669?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten","html_url":"https://github.com/hiddenmarten","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hiddenmarten/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-01-01T11:52:17Z","updated_at":"2025-01-01T11:52:17Z","body":"_Duplicate explanation of use cases from PR for the sake of context:_\r\n\r\nI encountered this issue when running rclone in Kubernetes. Let me provide a simplified Deployment manifest to explain the context:\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: apps/v1\r\nkind: Deployment\r\nspec:\r\n  template:\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n        - name: rclone\r\n          image: rclone/rclone:1.68.2\r\n          args:\r\n            - rcd\r\n          env:\r\n            - name: RCLONE_METRICS_ADDR\r\n              value: \":9000\"\r\n          livenessProbe:\r\n            exec:\r\n              command:\r\n                - rclone rc rc/noop\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this setup, the liveness probe fails because the `rclone rc rc/noop` command does not work correctly when the `RCLONE_METRICS_ADDR` environment variable is set. \r\n\r\nAs a workaround, we can modify the liveness probe command like this: `RCLONE_METRICS_ADDR=\"\" rclone rc rc/noop`\r\n\r\nHowever, this approach raises a concern: it's not immediately clear from the manifest why we are overriding the `RCLONE_METRICS_ADDR` variable. This lack of clarity could lead to confusion for others reading the configuration.\r\n\r\nAnother potential scenario to consider: If someone sets `RCLONE_METRICS_ADDR` globally in their `~/.bashrc` or `~/.zshrc` file, they may inadvertently prevent rclone from working correctly when running commands locally from the CLI. ","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rclone/rclone/issues/comments/2566975855/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"ey